verbose_text: Fibrinogen, ATIII, protein C, and protein S levels were all lower in the biliary versus hyperlipidaemic AP group (368.59 +/- 111.61 versus 498.34 +/- 115.08 mg/dl; 75.60 +/- 13.49 versus 80.63 +/- 9.59%; 79.53 +/- 18.21 versus 117.44 +/- 28.54%; and 73.42 +/- 19.40 versus 86.52 +/- 25.72%, respectively; all P < 0.05).
